            "answer_text": "No, although there are factors that hinder them: Microsoft are excellent at making stuff easy for average non techie users. Setting permissions and configuring firewalls goes against that a littleThe OS core predates the web and even disk borne viruses. Some deep parts never needed to fight non existent bad guysWindows is ubiquitous. If you are going to write a virus, targeting non techie users with an OS that is everywhere makes senseI\u2019m certain Microsoft never wanted to be an easy target. ",
